ion of new cultural ideas possible, while rising incomes and liberal attitudes created a generation of men behaving badly.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 03. Jan 2023) 4aEarly Modern Studies. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 7aART / European.2bisacsh  aLow Countries, Golden Age, youth culture, genderstudies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106628490 cprintz978946298302140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048532995?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048532995423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9789048532995/original  a978-3-11-066284-9  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK